   BUSINESS-TRAVEL (Undated) _ Priceline, the Internet auction
service that lets travelers bid for flights, is planning to expand
into hotels; Swiss World Airways, a new carrier, has begun flying
between Newark and Geneva; a new train links Copenhagen
International Airport and downtown; other items. By Janet Piorko.
</P>
<P>
   WORLDCOM-MCI (Undated) _ The cost of Worldcom's absorption of
MCI appears to be less than the company forecast. By David J.
Morrow.
</P>
<P>
   INTEREST-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ When the Federal Reserve Board
cut interest rates on Tuesday, almost nobody cheered. To stock
investors, the rate cut was too timid. To bond traders, the cut
signaled that they, more than the Fed, remain in charge of
interest-rate policy. And that means continued high Treasury prices
and a more-of-the-same flat yield curve, in which long-term rates
are as low as or lower than short-term rates. By Gretchen
Morgenson.
</P>
