years ago. She heard the doctors diagnose her in 1992 with terminal
esophageal cancer, and give her a year to live. Having been through
such an overwhelming, life-altering experience, she performed
almost a cleansing ritual: She documented her journey in her newest
book, A Season in Hell, a Memoir ($23, Knopf.) (Susman, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
