<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: DEATH VALLEY NATIONAL PARK 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Location: Death Valley National Park is located primarily in
southeastern California. A small part of the park _ Devil's Hole _
is in southern Nevada. The nearest major airport is in Las Vegas,
Nev., about a 2 1/2-hour drive from the park.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fees: The $10 per vehicle entrance fee is valid for seven
days. A tour of Scotty's Castle costs $8 ($4 for children).
</P>
<P>
   _ Accommodations: Campground rates range from $10 to $16 per
night. Reservations can be made by calling 800-365-2267. Hotel
accommodations are available inside the park at Stovepipe Wells
Village (rates start at $55; call 760-786-2387); Furnace Creek
Ranch (rates start at $85; call 760-786-2345); and the luxury
Furnace Creek Inn (rates start at $150; call 760-786-2361). Some
recreational vehicle camping facilities are available at Stovepipe
Wells.
</P>
<P>
   _ Information: Write to Death Valley National Park, P.O. Box
579, Death Valley, Calif. 92328; call 760-786-2331; or visit the
Web site: http://www.nps.deva/.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
_ Compiled by SYD KEARNEY &QL; 
Houston Chronicle &QL; 
