<P>
   STOCKS-QUARTER _ Market outlook and quarterly wrapup. Stocks are
finishing the quarter with a down day. The slide is being
attributed to end-of-quarter selling. The Dow is off 186 points and
the Nasdaq about 40. With year-to-date Dow. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   EATON-PLANTCLOSING _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Eaton Corp., reacting to
the prolonged semiconductor slump, will close its 239-employee
Austin semiconductor equipment plant and transfer its operations to
Massachusetts. (Ladendorf, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONWIDE-DISCRIMINATION _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Nationwide
Insurance, the country's fourth-largest insurance company, has
illegally discriminated against some Texans based on their race,
ethnicity and age, according to a state regulator who recently
recommended a record $10 million fine against the company.
(Elizondo Jr., Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SMALL-BIZ-COLUMN _ AUSTIN -- Snagging a contract with a big
company such as Dell Computer Corp. or IBM presents two issues to a
small business owner. First, the small business owner must get in
the door to make the pitch. Second, the owner must be ready for the
sudden increase in business with enough employees and money to get
the job done. Or is it the other way around ? (Tyson, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
