A2613 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CORRECTIVE-MA-RUTHARD     09-30 0087
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIVE-MA-RUTHARDT-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story MA-RUTHARDT (a),
by Bruce Mohl, which moved 9/29, will wish to use the following
corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe story incorrectly stated that Emlico walked away
from millions of dollars in environmental cleanup liability in
Massachusetts by liquidating in Bermuda. Actually, the insurer's
Bermuda liquidation spawned a legal fight between Emlico and
companies with which it had reinsurance contracts.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
</TEXT>
