<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This Weekend on TV
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Requiem for a Heavyweight'' (1962) 8 p.m. EDT on Turner
Classic Movies_ Rod Serling's fine adaptation of his celebrated
teleplay about a boxer at the end of his rope. Stars Anthony Quinn,
Jackie Gleason, Mickey Rooney and Julie Harris.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Witness'' (1985) 9 p.m. EDT on USA _ What the stars
(including Harrison Ford and Kelly McGillis) lack in sheer
celebrity force, director Peter Weir makes up with ambience and
pictorial flair in this intriguing tale of an Amish kid (Lukas
Haas) who witnesses a murder.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Epicurious'' 9:30 a.m. and 11:30 a.m. EDT on Discovery _
Discovery and Conde Nast combine TV and the Internet for a new food
show. First up: barbecued chicken and maple baked beans at 9:30 and
Lobster Newburg and French apple cake at 11:30. You watch the
show's hosts trek to microbreweries, maple syrup farms, fish
markets, oyster coves and other places as they ready dishes. When a
recipe perks your palate your learn more at www.epicurious.com.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Farm Aid'' 6 p.m. EDT on CMT _Country Music Television airs
six hours of the annual benefit concert. Among those performing:
John Mellencamp, Neil Young and Willie Nelson.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Sessions at West 54th'' (PBS-check local listings)_ David
Byrne hosts the second season of music shows. The kickoff includes
performances by Lucinda Williams and The Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``TLC Legends: OJ's Dream Team'' 10 p.m. EDT on The Learning
Channel _ Meet the guys who got Simpson off: Robert Shapiro,
Johnnie Cochran, F. Lee Bailey and Alan Dershowitz.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Cold War'' 8 p.m. EDT on CNN _ Episode 2 focuses on
1945-47, with Stalin demanding a buffer zone for the Soviet Union
in postwar Germany. Part of the result: Poland, Romania, Bulgaria
and Hungary become Soviet satellites. Color home movie footage
shows Winston Churchill in the tiny Missouri farm town where he
used the phrase ``iron curtain.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``A River Runs Through It'' (1992) 10 p.m. EDT on TBS _
Breathtaking photography fuels this pre-World War I family
fly-fishing tale in the way-out-there Northwest (specifically:
Montana). Stars Brad Pitt.
</P>
