<DOCNO> NYT19980930.0267 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-30 18:08 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2691 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-AIDA-REACTION-COX     09-30 0394
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AIDA-REACTION-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Reader's comments on ``Aida''
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA_Audiences adore ``Aida'' _ at least those who called us
to comment about ``Elaborate Lives: The Legend of Aida.'' Based on
what they saw in preview performances at the Alliance Theatre, a
large majority of the nearly 100 callers gave the musical an
overwhelming thumbs up. Some complained about the music's loud
volume, but most overlooked technical problems involving the show's
big special effect, a spinning, unfolding pyramid.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``I thought it was the best production of anything I've ever
seen: the best performance since my husband rationalized buying his
new convertible. Everything was fantastic, even though the pyramid
malfunctioned in the first half. And I got to see Elton John (at
the theater). The only thing I was less than ecstatic about was the
choreography.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Deborah DeHaven, Roswell , Ga.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``I loved it. It made me laugh, it made me cry. It was
emotional, sensual, funny. My favorite songs are ``Elaborate
Lives'' and ``My Strongest Suit.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Brenda Young, 43, Marietta , Ga.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``I loved it so much we got a second set of tickets. This is
going to be a hit.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Penny Linder, 50ish, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   -- ``It was fun, it was great. You could definitely feel the
Elton John-Tim Rice combination throughout. The songs were
wonderful. We got into it. I think it's a hit. It's a great way for
the Alliance to kick off its 30th-anniversary season. I thought it
was awesome, a fun night at the theater.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Jim Miskimen, 56, Tucker , Ga.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``It was fabulous. I cried a lot. It was one of the more
enjoyable plays I've seen, and I've seen many. The music is
amazing. The lyrics are totally inspiring. It was our 36th wedding
anniversary and we had a wonderful time.'' _Muriel Littman, 54,
Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   -- ``I'm the wrong age for rock concerts and I've never been to
one, although I think I just was. It was far too loud. Most of the
lyrics were absolutely drowned out. But I quite liked the show.
</P>
<P>
   _Marjorie Andrews, 67, Atlanta -- ``We thought it was absolutely
breathtaking. We could see the deep Disney pockets as far as all
the special effects. We look forward to seeing it again.''
</P>
<P>
   _Jackie Goodman, 49, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
