<P>
   CARRIER-INDEPENDENCE _ (Puget Sound Naval Shipyard, Wash.) _ It
was a moment of crisp ceremony and spontaneous tears as they
lowered the flag for the last time on the USS Independence. The
39-year-old aircraft carrier, until Wednesday the oldest warship on
active duty in the Navy, passed into history in a decommissioning
ceremony that drew senior Navy officials and scores of carrier
veterans from all over the nation.
