<SLUG> BC-CLINTON-JONES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PRESIDENT BALKS AT $1 MILLION DEAL WITH JONES
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ President Clinton conferred with his lawyers for
nearly an hour Wednesday about his next move in the Paula Jones
sexual misconduct lawsuit, and White House officials said he was
deeply reluctant to meet her price of $1 million to settle the
case.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Jones' lawyers have adopted a take-it-or-leave it strategy,
suggesting that they would consider reducing their demand by only a
small amount. The White House made a counteroffer last week saying
it would pay her $500,000 to settle the lawsuit, but Mrs. Jones'
team rejected that proposal immediately.
</P>
<P>
   The president and Mrs. Clinton were receptive to settling the
suit for the first time because Mrs. Jones has dropped her demand
that Clinton apologize to her.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
