NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, OCTOBER 1
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-BRADLEY-NYT (moved on Tuesday, September 29)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of former Mayor Tom Bradley of Los Angeles sent by
the New York Times News Service on Tuesday, September 29, referred
incorrectly in some copies to the landmark he attained with his
election in 1973. While Los Angeles had a significantly smaller
percentage of black voters than other big cities with black mayors,
Mr. Bradley was not the first black mayor of a largely white major
city; a majority of Cleveland's population was white when Carl B.
Stokes was elected mayor in 1967.
</P>
</TEXT>
