   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NORTHWEST-ECON (Kahlotus, Wash.) _ Here in what is by many
measures the most trade-dependent region of the country, Asia's
economic problems are clearly hitting home, starkly illustrating
the domestic downside of a crisis that in other parts of the United
States may still seem like an across-the-world abstraction. By Sam
Howe Verhovek.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo [NYT16) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-CIVIL-RIGHTS (Los Angeles) _ In what is believed to be the
largest civil rights judgment against law enforcement in
California, Los Angeles County has paid nearly $24 million to 36
people who sheriff's deputies arrested, and in some cases beat,
during a bridal shower in 1989. By Verne G. Kopytoff.
</P>
<P>
   HIGHWAY-GUARD-RAILS (Detroit) _ The Federal Highway
Administration is banning as of Thursday all further installations
of two popular kinds of guard rails along Federally financed
highways, after determining that the guard rails cause high-riding
pickup trucks and other vehicles to roll over during tests. By
Keith Bradsher.
</P>
