<P>
   QTR-WINNERS (Undated) _ Even after many lesser stocks had faded,
the United States' blue-chips sailed into the third quarter
seemingly headed for yet another year of improbably outsize gains.
But before long, the blue-chips joined the rest of the stock market
in a general slide, as an array of negatives came together at once.
By Robert D. Hershey Jr.
</P>
