<P>
   NY-RED-HOOK (New York) _ The Red Hook section of Brooklyn has a
spring in its step. But will it falter under 10,000 tons of the
city's waste a day? The old 48-acre Todd Shipyard here is one of
sites three in Brooklyn and one in the South Bronx that are
reportedly being considered for a garbage transfer station. By Anne
Raver.
