<HEADLINE>
BOWEN'S THOUGHTS ARE WITH WIFE, BABY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC offensive lineman Ken Bowen returned to
practice Wednesday after missing Tuesday's session to be with his
infant daughter, who is hospitalized in Oakland after being born
prematurely.
</P>
<P>
   Bowen also missed Tuesday's practice to clear up some
health-insurance problems but said his daughter, Katherine, is
doing fine even though she weighs just 1 pound, 12 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   ``They expected a lot of problems, but there haven't been,''
Bowen said. ``She's eating and aware of her situation.''
</P>
<P>
   The tough part for Bowen has been concentrating on football,
with his wife and baby up north.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's tough. It's always on my mind,'' he said. ``But I've
gotten a lot of support from my teammates and coaches.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Day off for Soward?: USC coach Paul Hackett said wide
receiver R. Jay Soward might sit out today's practice to rest his
sore ankle.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a little nicked,'' Hackett said. ``I'm a little
concerned. He didn't have his usual tempo today.''
</P>
<P>
   __ It's not jitters: Although quarterback Mike Van Raaphorst has
experienced food poisoning and flu-like symptoms before two games,
Hackett said he doesn't think the sophomore is being affected by
nerves.
</P>
<P>
   ``He doesn't strike me as the kind of personality where I would
worry about that,'' Hackett said. ``He's a pretty calm guy. I think
it's just a bad-luck deal.''
</P>
<P>
   Because Carson Palmer played nearly half of the Florida State
game, Hackett said he has evenly split snaps between the
quarterbacks this week. Practice had been divided 60-40, with Van
Raaphorst getting more snaps.
</P>
<P>
   __ Papadakis will start: With Chad Morton (strained back)
missing his second day of practice, Petros Papadakis will start at
tailback.
</P>
<P>
   Morton is expected to return to practice today.
</P>
<P>
   __ Cusano's back: Linebacker Mark Cusano pronounced himself
fully recovered from his ankle injury, although he will probably
have to wait another week to start.
</P>
<P>
   Cusano went 59 plays against Florida State, or about five more
plays than starter Zeke Moreno. He had four tackles; Moreno had
two.
</P>
<P>
   Strong safety Grant Pearsall has also been told he will wait
another week before starting.
</P>
<P>
   Another injured Trojan, quarterback Jason Thomas, has begun
riding a bicycle and working out in a swimming pool as he recovers
from ankle surgery.
</P>
<P>
   __ Rare score: USC beat Arizona State 21-14 in the College
Baseball World Series championship, but don't expect a similar
score Saturday. In 987 games, USC has had just one game end 21-14,
when the Trojans defeated No. 1-ranked Cal in 1951.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
