<HEADLINE>
TCU GETS TWO FOOTBALL COMMITMENTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TERRANCE HARRIS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas_ The TCU football program has received two
oral commitments for next fall.
</P>
<P>
   DeSoto quarterback Casey Printers committed late last night and
Dallas Bishop Lynch offensive lineman Matt Orlovsky made his
intentions known over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Printers, a 6-foot-4, 195-pounder, was considering Syracuse and
Notre Dame before deciding to remain close to home with the Horned
Frogs. The District 8-5A most valuable player last season after
completing 139 of 289 passes for 2,033 yards and 15 touchdowns,
Printers is an athletic quarterback with a strong arm.
</P>
<P>
   ``TCU is a program on the rise and I wanted to be a part of
that,'' said Printers, who has completed 53 of 90 passes this
season 707 yards, three touchdowns and three interceptions. ``Their
coaching staff is very good and very organized. You can tell they
are moving forward.
</P>
<P>
   ``And the offensive system is tailor-made for me.''
</P>
<P>
   Orlovsky, a 6-foot-5, 290-pound offensive lineman from the 5A
TAPPS program, said he was convinced after watching Saturday
night's 35-34 upset of then No. 23-ranked Air Force. Orlovsky had
been considering Rice, Duke, SMU and Purdue.
</P>
<P>
   ``That game sold me because I saw the enthusiasm Coach
\RDennis\S Franchione brought to his team,'' said Orlovsky, an
all-district and second-team all-state performer a year ago. ``You
can tell he's a sincere guy who really cares about his players.''
</P>
<P>
   The Frogs also received an oral commitment from 6-6, 280-pound
Waco Robinson offensive lineman John Glud in August. Oral
commitments are non-binding.
</P>
</TEXT>
